comment: RATR shows James (CLE) makes incidental contact with Mirotic (MEM) on his drive.
Noah (CHI) engages Mozgov (CLE) on Rose's drive, but does not affect his ability to defend.
Mozgov (CLE) makes contact with Rose's (CHI) body and the contact affects his shot.
Noah (CHI) establishes himself in the direct path of James (CLE) before the contact occurs.
Butler (CHI) sets the screen on Dellavedova (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Butler (CHI) makes contact with James' (CLE) body and the contact affects his shot.
James (CLE) clears out Dunleavy (CHI) with his elbow.
James (CLE) jumps vertically and remains vertical through the contact with Rose (CHI).
Blatt (CLE) attempts to call a timeout when none remain. None of the three officials saw Coach Blatt signal for a timeout.
Noah (CHI) jumps forward and bumps James (CLE) and the contact affects James' (CLE) shot.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the ball went out of bounds at 1.5 seconds and added .7 seconds to the game clock.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that James' (CLE) field goal was taken from behind the two-point line and before time expired was upheld.
